      "writtenOn": "2026-05-18T20:58:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe clarify here when there is a need for a session version bump \u0026 updating counters ? I can agree if we receive a SYN packet for a session in TIME_WAIT state (and we need to investigate the appropriate mechanisms to ensure the session version is incremented properly without side-effects), but what about a session receiving a re-transmitted SYN before a handshake is established ?",
      "revId": "a630eaaf346922c4f22f3bdced23faa2b2a7dc61",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
