        "id": 1263
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T11:28:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In CSIT tests, SYN either means retransmit (due to RX loss on receiver side) on the \"same session\", or a new client instance (after the old one is suddenly destroyed at the end of a trial) that happens to use the same 5-tuple deserving a \"new session\". In production, I suspect the important occurrences could come from SYN flood DDoS attacks, but I have no idea what is the appropriate reaction in SFDP code when that happens.\nIn other words, I think my current TODO comment is correctly formulated as a question, because I do not have the answer.",
      "parentUuid": "30234cb8_d948f75e",
      "revId": "a630eaaf346922c4f22f3bdced23faa2b2a7dc61",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
